						               													<description>In 1973 the band The Meeples broke up during the recordings for the Vinil album. The A-side of the unfinished album quickly became cult-followed by fans and critics around the world, turning into one of the most intriguing legends of Rock&amp;acute;n Roll history. 50 years later the band finally reunite and decide to finish the B-Side with the help of a team of the best musical producers in the show biz.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players must start their turn spinning the record's rondel on the turntable to choose an action within their reach or spend production points to achieve one of the other actions. After resolving these actions, players allocate audio cards to the five studio tracks, earning points and performing bonus actions if elements such as sound wave or time track position are matched.  Each round represents a song recorded on the A-side of the album that will help players gather information to aid inside B recordings.&amp;#10;After listening to all the songs on the A-side (6,7 or 8 rounds to 2,3 or 4 players respectively) the game ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player in your round allocate an audio card in a track and obtain victory points with the combination between: Buttons in that artist&amp;acute;s equalization track AND points in the studio track. Also, when a player allocates a guitarist card, each player that collaborated with the equalization of the guitar obtain victory points too.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whoever contributed the most effectively to the construction of the tracks on the B-side of the album and will be declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
